{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Debug and Fix CMS External Media Library Configuration Error\n\nResolve the CMS configuration error preventing the system from loading due to a missing external media library registration.\n\nProblem Summary:\nThe CMS fails to load with error message: \"Missing external media library 'default'. Please use 'registerMediaLibrary' to register it.\"\n\nRequirements:\n- Locate and review the CMS configuration file (config.yml)\n- Identify where external media libraries should be registered\n- Verify if 'default' media library is defined in the configuration\n- Register the missing 'default' media library using the 'registerMediaLibrary' method\n- Ensure the media library configuration includes all required parameters (storage backend, upload paths, access credentials)\n- Verify the media library initialization occurs before CMS attempts to use it\n- Test CMS loading to confirm the error is resolved\n- Validate media upload/retrieval functionality works correctly after fix\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Check if other media libraries beyond 'default' are also missing\n- Verify media library dependencies are installed\n- Ensure file system permissions allow media storage access\n- Confirm storage service credentials (if using cloud storage) are valid",
